values:
I don't know if anyone is still here that used to read my journal. Most people have moved to myspace or facebook. I have a myspace account myself, so if you are here and if you want look me up. :)

My life is very busy. I am also surrounded by drama, no matter how I try to avoid it. WoW is corrupted with it. Always something going on to upset or piss me off. Work is an exercise in self control or maybe self delusion. Not really sure. Can't really write what is happening, just incase, but it has me very nervous. I spent the month of Feb sick with an infected tooth and then pnumonia, so that not only sucked but put me behind a bit in my schoolwork. 

Well, this is just damn depressing so I am going to stop. I hope those of you who I haven't talked to in a while look me up. Should be able to find me on myspace under my name.

Last night I had a horrible dream about work. I've dreamt about work before, but this one has images that I just can't get out of my head. So, I figured if I write it out I can eject it from my mind. I will have to use initials due to confidentiatlity, but I think it will still be understandable.

It started at a bonfire at the bottom of a hill of a large estate like house. An old victorian with a wrapraound porch, out in the woods somewhere. Donald Sutherland was telling us stories as entertainment. Everyone I work with was there, along with three that no longer work at North Central, one that quit and 2 that were fired, and all of our clients. It was some kind of weekend get-away trip.

It was dark when Donald Sutherland was talking, but when he stopped the bonfire got brighter and as I looked to my right I saw 2 bodies hanging from tree branchs. The one closest to me was a client of mine who committed suicide last Christmas. I looked to the left and I saw another man hanging. I could tell that they were dead and that there was nothing I could do for them. I then noticed a large wooden box over to the side, it had some ornate carvings on it, and was worried that someone was hurt inside it.

So I ran over to the box, but it was empty. When I turned around everyone was gone but one client, VJ. The bonfire was gone, everyone had left, the bodies hanging in the trees were gone. VJ had a noose around his neck with the rope swung over a tree branch near were the bodies had been hanging. He was tugging on the rope with all of his might trying to kill himself. I ran over to him and asked him what he was doing and he told me he was trying to kill himself. For some reason I could not stop him and I knew that the only chance I would have was to get some help.

I started to run across the field, which seemed a lot bigger now, and up the hill. When I finally reached the house I saw an excoworker (the one that quit)smoking a cigerette outside. I asked her to check on VJ while I got more help and she started running down the hill. I ran inside the house and started screaming that I needed help. I heard a voice from the kitchen asking me what was wrong. I told them that VJ was trying to kill himself and I needed help. She stated that I didn't need to worry and was overreacting. That he did this all the time and wouldn't do anything. I stated that he had a noose around his neck and this was serious, and she laughed at me. 

At this point my mother walked down a staircase near me and said she would go with me. (I have no idea why my mom was there, except maybe the fact that I know I can always count on her) We run down the hill to see my coworker sewing up a canvas body bag over VJ's dead body. For somereason there was another bodybag beside her which I somehow knew had Donald Sutherland in it. I started to cry because I was too late to save him and my mother turned to me and said, "You could so get (a current coworker) fired." I looked at her and she said, "After what she said to you when you said VJ needed help she is so fired." I then woke up.

I have a few ideas of where this came from. I had a client on Thursday get sent home because he wasn't suicidal from the ER eventhough he was clearly paranoid and unable to care for himself. It is a year from when I took TLA to emergency services because he told me he was suicidal and they sent him home. He killed himself a few hours later. We are in the middle of licensing, and we failed last year. If our charts are not perfect within the next 2-weeks we could all lose our jobs right before Christmas. (The worst part is I don't know if that would be so horrible at the moment)Because of this everyone is stressed out and our bosses keep coming up with new and improved "policies" that need to implemented "yesterday". They fired one co-worker so we are all trying to help 8 clients when in reality it is impossible to do everything needed for more than 5. We have paper work we need to do on our new clients that we know nothing about. 

Yeah, that might be part of it, but damn that dream sucked.

I'm very sorry I have been neglecting this journal. School is keeping me very busy. I took two classes over the summer (Statistics and Forensic Psychology) and am currently taking another four (Research Design and Analaysis, Criminology, Social Psychology, and Sociology of the Family) and work has been very hectic. Seems like I always either have a client in crisis or my new boss is coming up with a new stack of paper work that needs to be done yesterday damnit!

I also still have my friday night game, Steve has been sick a lot lately, my cat has a heart condition and a hyper-active thyroid, we have a friend staying with us that is temporarily homeless, and I am assisting in running a guild in WoW. So, some things have had to fall to the wayside and unfortunately this was one of the first to go.

A quick update. We moved out of the city and into a smaller town. I really like it out here. It is quiet and our place is so much bigger. And we now have WINDOWS!!!! You do not understand how much that can mean to you unless you have lived in a place that lacked them. Windows just do not get the respect that they deserve. The only bad thing is my commute has gotten a lot bigger, which is hitting me in the time department also. I am now about an hour away from school and about 25 mins away from work. I end up doing a large circle every day because my classes are all in the morning.

I still work at North Central Human Services, but I'm looking for better employment. Now that I have a year and half in the feild I might be a little more marketable.

I also now have a myspace account, which you are all invited to come and see.  myspace.com/ember73  You need to ask to be my friend, some of my clients have accounts so I had to make mine private for obvious reasons. Its also why my phone is now unlisted, so if you want my number just send me a message.

As for email, I now have time warner cable and have not yet figured out how to access my account lol. I am going to try to remember to call them on Monday when I will actually be home while they are open.

I hope everyone is doing well and I miss you guys!

MATH 0200 01 Basic Math II Fitchburg State UG Day 3.5 
   
 PSY 2830 01 Socio-Emot & Person Develop Fitchburg State UG Day 4.0 

 PSY 2840 02 Developmental Psychopathology Fitchburg State UG Day 4.0 
   
 SOC 3000 01 Social Stratification Fitchburg State UG Day 4.0  
   
Not a complete 4.0 anymore, but I'll take it!

I wish I wasn't so busy, I miss sleep. Please forgive the spelling mistakes and typos that will run amuck in this as I am too tired to fix them. :P

Anyway, one of my classes was canceled today so I have a little time to kill before my next one.

Steve is doing better. He had his second set of x-rays which showed that the pnuemonia was gone, but that he still had some inflamation that could be a problem. He was supposed to have his pulmonary function test on Friday, but we had a random snow strom and we had to reschedule it for April 13th. Since getting out of the hospital he has been physically week and its nice to see him able to move around more freely again. Part of the delay was that he got hit with two nasty colds after getting home.

At work they have moved on to picking on one of my coworkers, which pisses me off more than when they picked on me. She a really good kid and works her ass of with the most difficult client we have in the company and I hate to see her railroaded. The girl I was having problems with is no longer giving me any trouble. All it took was doing her a favor one day and now we are cool again, which is good because I hate having issues with co-workers, its suppose to be us against management. I just wonder why this company is always picking on somebody. I just don't get it.

Let's see, what else is going on. School is still going well. Between work and Steve being sick I don't think I will manage a 4.0 this semester but I am learning to come to terms with it. I have to meet with my advisor soon to talk about summer and next year and I keep putting it off which is dumb of me, but time is something I hate giving up these days.

I guess that's about it. 

Oh, and I'm excited that our Werewolf game will be starting up again. Steve hasn't felt up to running since he got out of the hospital and I really miss it. I need the release of roleplaying to escape reality for a little while. 

I promise to update if anything new happens with Steve's health or something important happens, otherwise I am sorry I don't have much time these days, it should ease up soon.

I have a 1/2 an hour, so I will try to get as much out as possible and it will also explain why I have disappeared lately.

I'm going to attempt to go chronological, but anyone that knows me will realize how difficult that may become.

In December my dad had a stroke. He's doing ok, he has some minor nerve damage and he hasn't been aloud to go back to work yet, but he can walk and talk and the only change he has noticed is that he now gets car sick, when he never did before. They are having some trouble figuring out the medication because of the bleeding problems he has had because he is diabetic. The blood vessels behind his eyes have burst before and if they put him on too strong of a blood thinner to keep him from having another stroke then he could go blind. 

He has had an almost stroke sense then, I can't remember the initials they gave it, but basically it meant that he had a blood clot in his head, but it broke down before causing any damage. 

Now he's waiting to see if he can get on disability at least temporarily because his jobs plan is for people that are ill to use their vacation and sick time and he has run out.

Also in December one of my clients committed suicide. Actually he wasn't really my client anymore, he had been switched to a new girl a few weeks before, but I was the one he had worked closest with for the last 6 months. I was the last one to talk to him, and I knew something was wrong and took him to Emergency Services, but he contracted for safety so there was nothing that they could do. I was cleared in the investigation done by the Dept. of Mental Health, and I know I did everything I possibly could for him, but it still feels like maybe if I hadn't switched him to a new worker or maybe if I had said something different when he spoke with me... I know these feelings are normal and I really don't feel guilty or like I did anything wrong, but I still think about it. What surprised me is that my company didn't offer any counseling or anything to me or his currant worker. I thought it would kind of be policy to have me talk to someone when there was a death, but I wasn't even given a day off.

In January a dear friend of the family passed away. 

A couple of weeks ago Steve had to be rushed to the hospital. He's home now, thank God, but it was really scary. He couldn't breathe and when they hooked him up to the machines his heart rate was at 145 at one point and averaging 125-130 for over an hour. His blood pressure was high and his O2 saturation was low. If he hadn't gone to the ER he could have suffocated. He had asthmatic bronchitis and pneumonia. He's still on an inhaler and we have to go get another x-ray done and have a breathing test done to see if he has developed asthma, but he's doing a lot better then he was a week ago.

Work is getting me very stressed out, probably because of everything else going on in my life I am ill equipped to deal with it. Out of the 8 case managers I work with, 5 are on some sort of anti-anxiety or depression medication, 4 of them started taking medication after getting the job at North Central. My physical is later this month and the last time I went to my doctor she wanted to put me on something too. That can't be right, something is fucked up in that senerio. 

School is going well, but 3 of the classes I am taking are level 3000 which means lots of research and writing. Which is ok and I enjoy, but is also very time consuming. I am trying to go to school Monday, Wednesday, and Friday, and to work 10 hours on Tuesday, Thursday, and Saturday, and 8 on Wednesday. Making up the 2 hours I am missing by either doing an 11 hour shift or two or using my vacation time. That leaves Sunday for getting everything else done. I'm exhausted.

I also have 2 friends who are going through a really hard time and I am trying to help them through it. I feel like I am not being as good a friend as I could be though because my mind is in so many places right now.

Well, I gotta get to work.

Finals are over, and I think I did ok. I won't know for sure until after the holidays when grades are posted. 

Now I have to get ready for the next round of classes. I'm taking Basic Math 2 (so that I can get Statistics, Psychological Testing, and Research Methods 1 & 2), Social Stratification, Socio-Emotional Personality Development, and Developmental Psychopathology.

I'm not sure how work is going to handle my new schedule, which is why I took most of this week off, if they let me go I wanted to get all of my PTO (paid time off) used up so that I wouldn't lose it. They've fired people for less than saying that they needed to rearrange their schedule and they already fired the person who hired me and told me that they would be flexible and work around what ever classes I took as long as I was physically there 40 hours a week. If it comes down to it, my education has to come first. I have worked way too hard to let anything stop me now. Besides, they do not pay me enough to pay back my student loans. 

On a work/health/damn my insurance company straight to hell note...

I work in a basement, a damp, moldy, no windows basement. Myself and a few other of the girls I work with have environmental allergies. Mine have never bothered me all that much before, in the past I could just take a CVS brand allergy pill when the pollen count was really high and be fine, but being around an allergent 8 hours a day tends to be painful. Since I started working there I have had 3 sinus infections, black bags under my eyes, and headaches. After trying a few different medications my doctor finally prescribed two medications that made it so that I could go to work and still be able to breath at the end of my shift even if I was in the office all day. A pill and a nasal spray. With my insurance, the nasal spray is 10.00 a month, which is the lowest possible. When I ran out of free samples of the pill and went to the CVS to get my script it was 50.00 a month! I really can't afford that much every month. So I called my doctor and asked if I could get 3 months at a time that way I would only have a 50.00 bill every 3 months and they suggested I call my insurance company first because some of them bill by the month and the the script so I could end up with a 150.00 dollar bill. Called Fallon, may they rot in a pit of fire, and I was told that they do charge by the month. So I asked if there was an alternative medication, a generic of some kind that would be cheaper, and the lady informed me that no, all allergy medications were tier 3 and all tier 3 medications were 50 bucks a month no matter what. So I inquired about mail order or any programs they may have to help lessen the expense and was told no, they do not have any programs to make tier 3 medications less expensive only tier 1 (which cost 10.00) and tier 2 (which cost 25.00). I asked if there was anything that I may not be aware of that could help me and was very firmly told no that I would have to pay the 50.00. 

Glad to see that the cheaper the medication the more help they will give you to receive it. 

I called my pharmacist who told me that the medication I was taking does not have a generic yet and that the only thing close was an OTC medication that is not as strong.

I wonder what will happen if I ask work to pay for it since it is only needed for my work environment. I kinda like having a paycheck though.

And what's up with the Politically Incorrect Police? Santa is no longer PC. The people in my office are doing a Secret Snowman gift giving because Santa might offend someone who isn't Christian. Now, I could understand if they were doing a Secret Baby Jesus or Gift of the Cross thingamabob, but Santa? Sure, Santa was Saint Nick, but give me one icon or symbol that does not have some sort of hidden or down right blatant religious undertone. Wasn't a snowman a druidic symbol somewhere back in time? What's next? 

I have my Werewolf game tonight. Way back about 15 years ago (damn I'm old) I played a character who made a few tiny mistakes and accidentally fell to the Wyrm and turned a wee bit evil. Our current group is now going to have to face her. Steve wants me to play her to really freak out the rest of the game. It should be interesting. Or an abysmal failure. I'm going to shoot for interesting though. :)

I didn't vote for him, and I have no idea why Massachusetts keeps voting in the random Republican governor when we are one of the most liberal states, but we got the fucker and now he's decided to do one last parting piece of bad legislature before the new guy starts next month.

I was supposed to get a raise, a nice respectable 3% raise. It was approved by the Dept. of Mental Health on July 1st and I was going to get a nice retro check right before Christmas and was going to be able to shower my loved ones with less cheap ass gifts. Anyone who works in human services knows how little we make, especially when we depend on state funding or grants to pay our salaries. And for some God only knows reason, Massachusetts pays less than most states for social work. My guess is because we have more social programs than most areas and more people looking for the work due to how may Liberal Arts colleges we have. My co-worker's boyfriend who also works in the company, he runs the clubhouse work program for people on disability, went to a conference and they were talking salary and he found out he could double his salary if he worked in Hawaii and make almost half more if he worked in Georgia. Now, the cost of living in Hawaii is huge, but Georgia? Alas, I am a born and bred Yankee and don't think I could leave New England, although lately I have been tempted. Not that I would have any clue where to go.

The worst part is that one of my co-workers has been with North Central Human Services for 3-years and she has only seen a .03 cost of living raise in that time. And she makes less than I do because the industry standards were lower when she joined the company and they do not change the rate of pay for current employees when this happens. 

So, back to my original point, before leaving office the jackass of a Governor decides that one of the last things he is going to do in office is cut the funding to the Dept. of Mental Health, which was going to cover raises for all the peons that they pay. As a peon I am not very happy. Even if the new guy, Devol Patrick, decides to reinstate the funding I have still lost my retro check and am still going to be buying my loved ones cheap ass presents this Christmas. 

And Mit wants to run for president...

You think Bush is bad? Just wait and see what happens if the country gets all stupid and inbred and votes this idiot in office.

I hate being so busy. I owe everyone under the sun an email, my journal has holes the size of Texas in it, and I miss my friends. At least I know that when I'm done I will have accomplished something that I have wanted since I was a kid. I will be nice to have a degree and maybe a few letters after my name.

Anyway, heres the quicky update:

School: College is going pretty good. A did alright on my midterms getting an A in Art Appreciation, which shocked the hell out of me, and a B+ in Intro to African American Studies, which I can live with because the test was an exercise in mind reading and really had very little to do with "facts".

I had some trouble signing up for classes for next semester. First I was playing phone tag with my advisor and then when we finally hooked up it was 2 days after everyone else signed up for classes and a lot of the ones I wanted were full. That was really my fault as I should have been more proactive about getting an appointment even if her office hours were during the time I am at work. As it stands I have Basic Math 2 which I have to take in order to take Psychological Stats, which I need for Research Methods and Psychological Testing, Socio-psychological Development, Social Stratification, and Cultural Anthropology. I may switch things around a little to make my schedule a little easier on me if some people drop other classes and I catch it. 

So, I'm looking at a A/B average right now, which is a little disappointing seeing as at The Mount I was running on a 4.0 the last two years, but I have a lot more on my plate then I did then.

On a side school note there is a girl in my Fiction Writing class who is also in my Inro to African class. Her goal in life is to be an editor, so I probably shouldn't be so upset by what she says about my work, but damn is she brutal. I asked her after class today if she had read my story that we are work shopping tomorrow and she asks if I want her to be brutally honest or sugar coat it because she doesn't want to hurt my feelings. And I picked brutal honesty because frankly it was too late for sugar. Sugar coating doesn't mean much if you -know- the person is lying to you. Anyway, she plain didn't like my story, which was fine. She hated the main character and thought she was too young since the other character was 5 years older and it was creepy, which is fine also although its not like I had the two making mad passionate monkey love or anything, it was a sex free story. She said I should make her 17 or 18 instead of 16 so people could fantasize about it. I can see that. She said the plot was cliche and read like a cheesy horror movie. Ouch, that one stung a bit. That the characters reactions were unrealistic, although I thought I had made it pretty clear that the story wasn't based in any sense of reality. She was annoyed when I interrupted my dialog with other things and felt that I didn't put in enough details during the dialog, ok that can be considered constructive I can work with that. She ended with saying that there was nothing really redeeming about my story but she would tell me more when we workshop tomorrow. Great, can't wait. I knew it wasn't a glorious piece of writing, hell it was only a second draft, but to tell me that there was noting good about it at all seemed a bit harsh. Really makes me want to write more...

Work: Is odd right now. They finally let us know that Robin left. She was under investigation and quit. They have 2 people sort of in charge of us and neither of them want the job. One reacts by being our friend and the other by being a total bitch because she is pissed that they put her in charge. I'm not sure if I will be able to work there next semester because of my school schedule, I'll have to see if I can work something out.

Life: Don't have much of one at the moment. I'll get back to you on that one.

I was at work again, this time in Gardner. I was waiting for a client outside of an apartment building. The client was either Uma Thurman or Cameran Diaz, I can't really remember which. Anyway, I was talking with a girl I do not know who was shadowing me and I told her that Uma/Cameran was probably going to be moving into her boyfriends house because he is a werewolf and that maybe I could get her apartment and just pay her the rent. I said the only problems with that is that a. a lot of vampires live in the building and they all need services and b. if she ever moved I would be evicted. She didnt come back so we walked back to the office. I had another client (a real one this time, same one as the last dream infact) waiting for a quarterly meeting and there were people still in the conference room. I peeked in and it was an All Staff meeting that I had forgotten about. 

Pam, who is one of my two sort of immediate bosses until they replace Robin, asked if she could talk with me. She pulled me into the bathroom and handed me my paycheck, but she pulled off the part with all the information about deductions and such. I looked at the check and it was for 1,300.00 for two weeks pay which is more than double what I make now after taxes and bennifits. On the top of the check was written on hold. She told me that she was waiting for the final approval to give me the raise and that it just came in but not to tell anyone else how much I got because all my coworkers were getting less money. I left the bathroom and ran into Robin who told me I deserved the raise because I said I could double my productivity if I had a short stock (no idea what this means, I was even confused in the dream) and it had worked. 

I then find myself drinking beer with my coworkers at one of their homes. I mention that Robin said we were all getting raises and the response vary from fat chance, to cold day in hell. So I decide to wait on telling them anything about my check.

I have one more client to visit and I go to his house. He turns out to be Lance Hendrickson. I walk up the stairs to his door and hear a meow. I look and Gizmo, my mother-in-laws cat who ran away was rubbing up against my leg. I pat the cat and ask her how she got there. She just purrs at me. 

So, Lance Hendrickson lets me and Gizmo in and by the time we get in the door, Gizmo turns into a little blond girl probably about 5 years old and Lance Hendrickson turns into Steve. So I tell the little girl "lets go we found your daddy" and she looks horrified, I get horror movie music and she raises her arm to point at the radiator. I look and see that Steve has been hogtied and is gagged behind the radiator. I look back at Lance Hendrickson and he picks up a giant stapler from his stove top and is going to attack me with it. I realize that I am going to die unless I give into the light.

So I close my eyes and a golden light starts to envelope my entire body and then it shoots out at Lance Hendrickson just before he is about to hit me with the stapler.

You would think that a company who's sole purpose is human services would have a basic understanding on human behavior. 

I'm pretty sure my immediate boss got fired or quit. Two weeks ago she took 2 days off....and never came back. Her desk was cleaned out on the Sunday following her two day vacation, everything is gone, pictures, files, her pen holder. Last week we started asking when or if she was coming back and we got a variety of responses, none of which was an answer. The over all favorite seems to be a change of subject all together. Now there are only 2 people left in the office when there should be 5. We got a message saying who to call instead of Robin, but no mention what so ever of why or for how long.

This is of course unsettling for us little people. We have no idea who to report to, who to go to with emergencies, what the hell is going on beyond our corner of cubicles. It's breding paranoia, confusion, fear, and we all work with the mentally ill, not a great cobination. 

We've heard that she quit, that she was fired for screwing up some paperwork, that she forged someones name, that she screwed up someones medications, that she signed something she didn't have permission to sign. I've been thinking of starting my own rumor that she was kidnapped by Amazon Cat Ninja Space Pirates it'd have as much fact backing it up as any of the other ideas. You think they would have learned there lesson after the first firing. Everyone is crying, us peons are assuming the worst thinking someone died and when asked they werent allowed to tell us, but I guess not.

Since I've worked there 3 people have quit and 5 or so have been fired. Only 2 have been replaced. Things are starting to fall between the cracks simply because those of us still there do not have the time or energy to get everything done. I see bad things on the horizon, I think I might want to start looking elsewhere.

Thank you all for your birthday wishes. I had a good day! :) I did practically nothing lol which is always a good thing. 

I got hit with about 500.00 in car emergencies last month, so my whole getting caught up with bills had to be postponed a bit, but at least it is only a bit. I have high hopes for this month considering I just put in 11.5 hours of OT this week. 

My job is both good and bad, but I guess you can say that about any job. We keep having people leave, mainly because our immediate management is a bunch of high school drama queens, and the moment I have 8 clients I am responsible for. As long as they hire someone soon and I get put back down to 5 or 6 I should be fine, but there just isn't enough hours in the day to give 8 people what they need and/or want from me. And the paperwork is going to take me longer than the scheduled amount of time I have to do it. It's strange, you'd figure the clients would be the stressful part of my job seeing as I now work with 3 boarder line personality disorders, 2 bi-polar disorders, 1 factious disorder, 7 major depression, 2 with serious physical problems, 1 with mild mental retardation and 6 schizophrenics (one of which has a "controller" who prevents him/her from taking care of him/herself, but it's my manager that makes me munch on Advil when I get home. We are treated like disposable employees and while I have only been the subject of her ire once (with a hysterical yelling at in staff meeting because I didn't know I had to inform her of a client going to the hospital for a physical reason, I did inform everyone else I was suppose to and wrote it in the book that everyone is suppose to read daily with lines like "If "client" had died we all would have been fired! You could have lost everyone in this room their job! Go to the hospital right now!") She has this kind of reaction to one of us back there at least once a week, usually for things that we were never told where policy or things that out of our control. One person quit and left 15 or so progress notes unwritten. One of my coworkers ended up having to do about 10 of them and her job was threatened if it wasn't done on time. Another got yelled at because she took the company car that she had signed out when unbeknownst to her someone one else needed it for an emergency. We all go yelled at for going to Chinese buffet restaurants and taking hour long lunches when it never happened and for dressing like sluts while she was wearing a shirt cut so low it was embarrassing to look at her. And she has rather large breasts, so it was very hard not to laugh when she gave us the "no tits, ass, or stomach can be shown" rule.  

I'm not sure what is going to happen. Right now there are seven of us back there. One is about to quit because he just got his masters degree in counseling, one is about to be promoted to running a residence house, and one is getting married and moving to Germany in December. They fired the only person in the company that had Red Cross certification to train us in medication dispersal. We are down to one person in the company that can prescribe medication. One of our two Rehabilitation specialists just gave her notice. They fired one of the psychologists. The place is slowing falling to pieces. I hope they start replacing some of these people soon. On the up side, I became a little more valuable because I got my med training down a week before they fired the trainer.

College starts up again next Wednesday. I am taking four classes. On Monday and Wednesday I will be taking Art Appreciation at 8am and Introduction to African American Studies at 9:15am and on Tuesday and Thursday I will be taking World Civilizations 1 at 8am and Fiction Writing at 9:15. Then on Tuesday - Thursday going to work for 11 - 7 and my normal 9 - 5 on Friday and 12 - 8 on Saturday. My life is about to get very hectic. I couldn't go to school at night because they didn't have a Psych major at night, not that I'm taking any Psych classes this semester, but at least I'll be getting some of the random crap out of the way and I am looking forward to Fiction Writing. I also had to find classes that fit in the 8 and 9:15 time slots so I could still work 40 hours. 

Well, I guess that's about it for now. :) Talk to you all soon.

On to updates and stuff. The IRS thing isn't working out. A couple of weeks ago they called me and said that I wasn't showing a record for having paid taxes in 04, and I said that I have filed the same way since 95 when I got married so they gave me a number to call. I call the number and the lady says that yes I did file and she has no idea why the other office would not being showing the record and I ask her if she can email confirmation to the first woman. She said sorry but she was not allowed access to email. Which I was shocked about, who doesn't have email when you work with computers? So I call lady number one up and tell her and she's all shocked and says that the office may just not be cleared for email. She says she'll look again and call me back, which she does less than 15 mins later saying that she found me in the semstem. A week later they call and offer me a spot in training, but it is when I am in class. So I ask if there are any other shifts, the paper said they had days and weekend shifts, and lady number 3 says no. So I think and could probably still rearrange my Monday and Wednesday classes which would make me available every night but Thursday and she says no, you have to work all 5 nights of the week there is no flexability. So, I'm on standby. I passed all the tests and if someone fails or drops out of training for a day or weekend shift they will call me. I sent out an application to Smith and Fitchburg State, so hopefully I will have a clearer idea what kind of work I can look for soon. That will be helpful. I gotta go study for a test in Mass and the Federal Justice System. I promise to talk more later. :)

My interview is tomorrow and I am looking forward to finding out if I'm going to catch a break. If I don't that's ok too, I am still moving forward with school and even if its hard right now I know that things will get better financially. Sometimes I forget that and bitch and moan but deep down I know I am doing everything I can to progress and that sooner or later it will pay off. Its just hard sometimes to remember that fact when life gets so confusing and painful.

I am able to focus better now because I finally made a decision that I did not realize was a symptom of a greater decision I had been struggling with. You see the whole world of warcraft guild situation and if I should stay or go was just the tip of the iceberg of the enigma that was my feelings of depression and despair. I should have picked up on it sooner, I am not the type of person to get wrapped up in something as silly as a video game and the time I spent on the game was relatively minor in comparison to the time I spent on school and my relationships. 

I finally quit the guild and the only bitterness I feel about the act of quitting is that I have no idea if anyone had anything to say about the reasons I gave for leaving or if anyone posted any questions that I needed to clarify. I was denied access to the guild part of the forum pretty quickly after saying goodbye and while this is understandable as it is a guild forum and I am not a member anymore, it hurts only in the sense that other people that are not and never were members of the guild had and continue to have access to the forum. But this just confirms that my reasons and the decision I made were the right one. 

I can walk away knowing that I tried. The last few months I am sure that I have not been the best person to be around. I have been dealing with a few personal issues that I am sure made me cranky and easily offended by things that I normally would have let go, but if all it takes is a few months of me being a little more needy and a little less observant than normal for people to turn their backs on me as too annoying to deal with I am better off without them. I fear that the fact that I did not want to air the private problems that may have told more than the person I was having problems with may have wanted gave the impression that I was angry with people who I had already worked out my problems with or didn't have a problem with to begin with though. I hope that the email I got from one friend already has fixed part of that, and I hope that others will talk to me about how they feel, but I can no longer let it affect every aspect of my life.

You see, I really love people and believe that everyone has good in them. Even Matt who hurt me very deeply I believe is a good man. I was losing sight of this with the constant drama and feelings of resentment that were flowing from all directions including my own. I did the best I could to work things out with the people that I had a problem with, but if my best is not enough I am not going to beat myself up over it anymore. 

There in lies the real problem that I didn't know existed: I can not control how other people think or feel about me and it is ok that some people do not like me, even if they refuse to tell me why.

The other problem that I was trying so hard to ignore is that while I care very much for someone I can not kill myself to prove it. That there comes a point when it is obvious that nothing I do will change they way they think I feel or the motives behind my actions. 

The thing I have the most difficulty with is the fact that I am not responsible for the emotional health of my friends. This is more of a real life problem rather than an on-line life problem, but I have to get to the point where I can realize that as long as I am doing what I can to be there for people in need I am not responsible for their mental health. 

I have been dealing with the health problems of someone I love, Steve's mother who's view on reality is one of the hardest things to deal with, a friend who is bi-polar and going through a severe manic episode, a friend who is bi-polar and going through a time that may lead to a depressive episode, financial problems, trying to get into a good college for next fall, keeping my grades up when I am having problems concentrating, getting every little cold and flu that looks at me funny because my immune system is so tied to my emotions, a friend who's daughter just tried to kill herself and was aloud to sign herself out of the hospital because she is over 18, a family member whose company recently folded, some physical problems of my own, my apartment falling into disarray because I have not had the energy to clean things that Steve can not because he is allergic to dust, coming to terms with the fact that I will not be financially secure enough to adopt a child until I will be too old to be a good prospect for child services, fighting with masshealth because of being on unemployment, trying to be everything to everyone and therefore failing to be anything to anyone, spending time, thought and money on someone to send him a Christmas present that would mean something only to have it ignored, getting prepared for the heaviest semester of my college carrier so far and worrying that my gpa will drop, feeling powerless to help people who I would do anything for.

So, I'm going to give myself a break. If I am not permitted to be off center for a while then screw anyone who doesn't want to find out why or simply doesn't have the energy to care.

The last couple of months have been trying to say the least. I've had so many things going on that I haven't had the time to write any of them down. So this entry is going to jump around...a lot...and will try to explain why I feel like my brain is on the verge of exploding. The worse part is that every time I feel like things are starting to calm down it just picks up again. Not that my life is a complete shit salad.

Ok, where to start. I guess school would be a good place. I managed to get A's in all the classes I took last sememster, which is a good thing. It puts my overall gpa at 3.8 and my major gpa at 3.98. Forensic Psychology was a test of patience. I still feel like the college dropped the ball on that one and it was hard to finish 3 months of work in 3 weeks so that I could finish the class by last sememsters deadline. Next sememster is going to be busy, but it will have me graduating with an associates degree in human services in May. From January to March I will be taking Massachusets and the Federal Justice System from 4:30 - 7:30 on Monday and Wednesday and Counceling Methods and Interviewing Techniques from 7:30 - 10:30 also on Monday and Wednesday. From March to May I will have Counceling Methods and Interviewing Techniques 2 from 7:30 - 10:30 on Monday and Wednesday. From January to May I will also be taking the Psychology of Death and Dying on Thursdays from 4 - 7. So, with Tuesdays being a tentative game night for Rifts or Hunter if the game starts up again and Friday being Werewolf night, I will be a very busy woman. I am also taking Health and Fitness over intersession, which in January 3 - 9 from 9 to 1:45. I figured it would be easier to just get it out of the way and not take all 5 classes in the semester. 

I spent most of Novemeber and early December writing papers. Which I have a knack for, but having so many due at the same time and having to write so many complicated ones for Forensic Psychology was very taxing. I am very glad I got it all done on time.

I also need to start getting my shit together to apply to a four year college and the task is hanging over my head. I really should get that started, I have a feeling that if I just get going with it it will be easier than I think.

Christmas was nice, we went to my brother's house and the neices were cute and we usually have a nice time with my family. I was very tense the week of. I still had 2 more things to buy and needed my unemployment check to get them and this was the one week it was late. I usually get the check on Tuesday and didn't get it til Friday which meant shopping on Christmas eve, which just plain sucks. I got it done though which is what matters.

It felt weird not going to Steve's mothers house after my brothers though. I mailed her a card and then mailed her a few Christmas presents and still no contact. It amazes me how much of a bitch she is being. It has been over 6 months since she wrote us off. And frankly she really had no reason for being so pissed off in the first place, and I can't imagine my mother allowing that to happen. Of course she does that. She has the biggest paranoid streak I have ever seen in a person. I'm not sure how I feel about this, but I have made overchures and she has ignored them. I don't see how she can not realize that this is hurting her more than anyone else. I really don't much to do with most of Steve's family anyway and he is very happy about that.

This has been a rough time for Steve too. His foot has been swollen off and on for a month. He's been in pain and I have been under a lot of pressure which leads to stupid arguements between us that would not happen if we were both in better states of mind.

And there is so much more, but I just don't have the energy to finish this right now. I'll write more tomorrow.
